label: A5B6_hP33_151_3a2b_3c-001
title: V$_{6}$C$_{5}$ Structure
comments:
This is the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_hR2_166_a_b-001}{CuPt ($L1_{1}$) structure} with one of every six carbon atoms removed.  Placing carbon atoms on another (3a) site with $x = 1/9$ will restore the $L1_{1}$ structure. 
 (Venables, 1968) put this structure in space group $P3_{1}$ \#144 or its enantiomorph $P3_{2}$ \#145.  (Cenzual, 1991) showed that with the given coordinates the space group is actually $P3_{1}12$ \#151.
